  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Investment Associate",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Financial Modeling & Analysis:</strong> Building, maintaining, and reviewing complex valuation models (DCF, LBO) and analyzing financial statements.</li><li><strong>Deal Execution & Due Diligence:</strong> Assisting in the full deal lifecycle, including market research, industry analysis, and managing the due diligence process with advisors.</li><li><strong>Investment Memos & Presentations:</strong> Drafting investment proposals, pitch decks, and presentations for investment committees or stakeholders.</li><li><strong>Portfolio Monitoring:</strong> Tracking and reporting on the performance of existing portfolio companies, identifying risks, and recommending actions.</li><li><strong>Relationship Management:</strong> Liaising with founders, management teams, and external partners. </li></ul><p><strong>Key Requirements & Skills</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Experience:</strong> Generally 1–4 years in private equity, investment banking, consulting, or corporate finance.</li><li><strong>Technical Skills:</strong> Advanced proficiency in Excel, financial modeling, and valuation techniques.</li><li><strong>Education:</strong> Degree in Finance, Economics, or related field; CFA or MBA is often preferred.</li><li><strong>Competencies:</strong> Strong analytical thinking, attention to detail, commercial awareness, and excellent communication skills. </li></ul>",
